<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 06 at 4:15PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central Judith
Basin and southwestern Fergus Counties through 500 PM MDT...
At 415 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hobson, or 19 miles west of Lewistown, moving southeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Moore.
This includes Highway 200 between mile markers 56 and 58, and between
mile markers 60 and 75.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM MDT for
central Montana.</instruction>
